news_header: F-Secure is initiating change negotiations that may lead to job losses.
news_text: F-Secure is restructuring its operations, which may threaten up to 37 jobs in Finland as part of a broader plan that could affect up to 60 employees globally. The change negotiations will impact the company's sales, marketing, services, and technology sectors. Currently, F-Secure has around 360 employees worldwide, down from 530 at the end of September.
